editorialSummary.text: Sceney spot that's both a chic lounge with DJs & a modern steakhouse serving prime cuts & seafood.

originalText.text: I actually wanted to go for a happy hour drink to wait for some friends before dinner and see a Broadway show. The two bars were packed with customers, with no space to sit or stand, so we decided to stay for dinner. The hostess will not seat you unless the entire party is there. The atmosphere was pleasant and energetic. I find the tables a bit too close together. Dinner was nicely presented. Service was good and they understood that we had a show to catch.

originalText.text: This experience was exquisite. I got there and my server was Atom amazing guy. He shared stories about funny experiences while we waited for the rest of our party to arrive and they were hilarious. Atmosphere was great and the seats were very comfortable and spacious. Once I ordered my food I barely had to wait at all. My one and only complaint was that I felt the mashed potatoes lacked consistency and structure. Otherwise the food was perfect. My steak(medium 10 ounce) was delicious. Extremely tender on the inside and nice and crispy on the outside. As I took my first bite I was immediately impressed.The bread  which came before hand was the perfect appetizer. It came with garlic paste and perfectly suited my taste buds. For my drink I got the Shirley temple which I highly recommend. If you’re looking for pictures it’s the right choice. Overall this was an amazing experience and if you’re looking for something nice and a little pricy then this is the place to go.

originalText.text:
Wanted to try the happy hour here heard about it from a friend. First the bad then I'll go into the good. We arrived and the bar was packed. It was clear that the staff doesn't want to rush to help anyone looking for happy hour. They don't want to clear off tables and really want to push you to a dinner table. We waited 20 minutes to be seated with little to no acknowledgement.
While we were standing we smelled the scent of vomit as did the manager who acknowledged it's smell and walked away. Don't expect the service you receive from a traditional steak house like sparks or Gallagher's....

Now the good.
After you do get a seat the service was rather good and the food was great for the price. Top highlights were the short rib quesadillas and tater tots. We would probably try a different location and see if these items were isolated to this location.
Also I'm not sure I would come here for high end steak I would stick to the traditional ones. But highly recommend the happy hour for a quick bite. Just dont make this a first date because no one will be happy waiting for a table when there are so many dinning room tables empty.

originalText.text: One of the most beautiful restaurants I ever visited! Loved the environment! Such a fantastic decor & atmosphere! We just went in without a reservation and I was so happy we could get a table. The seating hostess was very kind & we loved our table! But the rest of the experience was a clear 3/5. The management’s marketing strategy to ask waiters to be pushy on expensive dishes, I presume, because our waiter practically ruined our dinner. He was so pushy,talking all the time. We got so tired of him. At the end, we just took what he suggested, as he was swearing we would enjoyed it… I wanted my steak very juicy, to be cooked in butter and showed him the dish from one of the restaurant’s photos. He said they did not have it anymore,but that if I would take the 110 dollar steak, they would make it like I wanted. As a result, I got a very dry steak with just a teaspoon of butter on top that they melted on the meat in front of me. No use. It was so dry I could not eat it. We ordered fries and in THIS restaurant they were premade! Defrosted! Tasteless! No info about this from the waiter. His was so focused into pushing us to order the most expensive dishes that he did not do his job: he did not inform us about the food. He strongly suggested the new dish of tempura prawns which we got but never told us that it was spicy. It is not an exaggeration to say his attitude ruined our evening. All this talking and pressure & the bad food at the end. Had it not been for such a fantastic atmosphere, I would grade our experience with 1
